
Overview of noun counterbalance

The noun counterbalance has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                 
1. (1) counterweight, counterbalance, counterpoise, balance, equalizer, equaliser -- (a weight that balances another weight)
2. balance, equilibrium, equipoise, counterbalance -- (equality of distribution)
3. counterbalance, offset -- (a compensating equivalent)

Overview of verb counterbalance

The verb counterbalance has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                 
1. (1) compensate, counterbalance, correct, make up, even out, even off, even up -- (adjust for; "engineers will work to correct the effects or air resistance")
2. oppose, counterbalance -- (contrast with equal weight or force)
3. counteract, countervail, neutralize, counterbalance -- (oppose and mitigate the effects of by contrary actions; "This will counteract the foolish actions of my colleagues")
